The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 August is 60,250 (6,944.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 August, there were 2,435 new confirmed cases (280.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 July, there were 2,145 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 14% (290 extra cases).
